  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add them to a baking tray, drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong>, season with <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then put in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>crispy potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1637144545592-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1637144545592-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1637144545592-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1637144545592-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1637144545592-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Deseed the<strong> pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1637144548878-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1637144548878-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1637144548878-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1637144548878-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1637144548878-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> pepper strips</strong> and<strong> sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 7-9 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for a further 1 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1637144553094-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1637144553094-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1637144553094-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1637144553094-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1637144553094-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, then stir in <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> to the softened pepper and onion and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened slightly</p><p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p><p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1637144557164-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1637144557164-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
